{
  "stem": "9730.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They, they were discussing it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they also improvised a certain code in, in which they-- I mean, it was a fairly innocuous code-- but, but in which they would let us know that things were really going from bad to worse.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I remember a letter, early on, in which my-- and, and we must have agreed on, on, on that name-- in which my mother said, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] as far as Aunt Dora's illness is concerned, I am afraid the prognosis is not very good.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It will only get worse, and-- a fact we all regret very much.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in, in my case, I, I am particularly sorry because we had such amiable times with her and, and, and, and really had a good time with her.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, and it's too bad that it had to come to this.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that meant, of course-- Aunt Dora was the code word for anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And later on, they would find other ways of describing things that they felt might go through censorship and they didn't want to say openly.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- I only remember that we devised this Aunt Dora thing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The other things became obvious, and we had to sort of figure them out as, as we went along.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But, in fact, in going over those letters so many years later-- let's say 40 to 45 years later-- it was even more difficult to remember what my mother might have meant by certain things.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I can, I can tell you one other that will give you an idea of, of what she said.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I remember getting a letter in 1938 in which she said, lately Mr.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Stresemann has surfaced again here, but I'm afraid to absolutely no avail.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
